body:
We're generating things like this:

```
 initial begin
    automatic logic [41:0] _T_3 = `THING;
    // indented too far!
        automatic logic [41:0] _tmp_8;
        automatic logic [41:0] _tmp_9;

    `ifdef FOO
      `ifdef BAR
        _tmp_8 = _T_3 ^ _T_3 ^ _T_3 ^ _T_3 ^ _T_3 ^ _T_3 ^ _T_3 ^ _T_3 ^ _T_3 ^ _T_3 ^ _T_3 ^ _T_3;
        _tmp_9 = _T_3 ^ _T_3 ^ _T_3 ^ _T_3 ^ _T_3 ^ _T_3 ^ _T_3 ^ _T_3 ^ _T_3 ^ _T_3 ^ _T_3 ^ _T_3;
        regValue = _tmp_8 ^ _tmp_9;
      `endif
    `endif
  end // initial

```

Because the expression temporary is being generated from the ifdef region but the temporary has to be put out in the enclosing scope.
